# Token Budget — Eager Context

Claude Code loads these files on EVERY conversation turn. Keep them lean.

## Budget limits

| Component | Limit | Current |
|---|---|---|
| CLAUDE.md | 1,600 tok | — |
| Rules (path-scoped) | ~350 tok each | — |
| Agents | ~350 tok each | — |
| Skills metadata (descriptions) | ~100 tok each | — |
| **Total eager** | **~6,100 tok** | **—** |

## Per-component limits

- Each path-scoped rule: max 350 tokens
- Each agent: max 350 tokens
- Each skill description: max 100 tokens (~50 words)
- CLAUDE.md: if exceeds 1,600 tokens → move to path-scoped rules

## Maintenance rules

- Before adding to CLAUDE.md: can it go in a path-scoped rule instead?
- Before adding a rule: does it really apply to ALL contexts in that path?
- Before adding a skill: will it be used at least 1x/month?
- Verify budget: `python .claude/count-context-tokens.py` (if available)
